The books intervening between the twenty-second and twenty- sixth give the events of the war for the years 216-212 ac. The operations are carried on in Italy, Spain, Sicily, and Africa. Livy's narrative passes quite abruptly from one scene of warlike events to another. The twenty-third book describes the movements of Hannibal in Samnium and Campania Í¾ his occupatiori of Capua, capture of near-by Casilinum, and his attempt on Nola.
